From 7f7b000426e8c192dddfe00631d16dc2c5d18583 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: patch <patch@local>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 13:46:11 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] serial: serdev: add PiBridge serial device driver for RevPi

Add the PiBridge serdev driver used by Revolution Pi (RevPi) devices to
communicate with I/O extension modules (DIO, AIO, etc.) over the PiBridge
serial bus.

The driver provides the low-level serial communication layer that the
piControl out-of-tree module uses to exchange data with RevPi digital and
analog I/O modules connected via the PiBridge connector.

Components:
- drivers/tty/serdev/pibridge.c: Main driver with IO and gate protocol
- drivers/tty/serdev/pibridge.h: Internal header for packet structures
- drivers/tty/serdev/pibridge_trace.h: Ftrace tracing support
- include/linux/pibridge_comm.h: Public API header for piControl module

Source: https://gitlab.com/revolutionpi/linux/-/tree/devel/revpi-6.18
Signed-off-by: Local Build <local@build>
